It is easy to become overwhelmed when you decide to start challenging accepted opinion. You become bombarded with new information. It quickly becomes overwhelming and difficult to know what's really true. It can also incredibly frustrating dealing with people may dismiss your ideas simply because they challenge the norm. Here are a few rules of thumb I recommend: 1. Keep a skeptical mind and remember that the narratives propagated by anyone, mainstream or fringe, is never the full story. Just because the government/media/whoever isn't telling the truth, that doesn't mean that anyone peddling an alternative viewpoint knows what they're talking about. 2. Remember that it isn't your personal responsibility to "wake up" everyone you come into contact with. Not everyone is ready to hear difficult truths or has the free time to do the necessary research. If you come across someone who seems open-minded you can point them in the right direction, but if you go around trying to convert everyone, you'll just drive yourself crazy and annoy all your friends. 3. Focus on the things in your life you do control. It's easy to get obsessed with the machinations of the wealthy few who treat the rest of us like chess pieces, but there is only so much you can do to fight back in the short term. However, there's quite a lot you can do to make yourself less dependent on the system: start a garden, learn how to do your own plumbing, eat fewer processed foods, etc. 4. On a similar note, get your finances in order. Learn how to earn income without relying on job where you're making money for someone else. There are lots of ways you can earn passive income online. You just have to be willing to do the research and see what fits your skill set. For longer term finances, I recommend investing in precious metals, but other people might advise looking into cryptocurrencies or other strategies. 5. Finally, look after your mental and spiritual health. You aren't going to help anyone by wearing yourself ragged or becoming so preoccupied with things out of your control that you can't enjoy life. All the bad stuff you just found out about has been going on for a very, very long time. Evil people have existed for as long as people have existed, but so have those who stood against them. New communications technology have made it increasingly difficult for the powerful and corrupt to hide their misdeeds. I do believe the "good guys" (for lack of a better term) will win in the end, but that will take time. The best thing you can do is practice self-improvement and keep yourself healthy so you're prepared for whatever the future throws at you.
